<DOC><DOCNO> AP900629-0235 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-29-90 0924EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     06-29 0146</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0155</SECOND><HEAD>London Stocks Higher Following Flurry in Futures Market</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Prices advanced on London's Stock Exchange Fridayfollowing a late flurry of activity in the stock index futuresmarket.   Traders said three major security houses were buying stocksrelated to the June Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock indexfutures contract, which expired in the morning.   At midday, the FT-SE 100 index was up 21.9 points, or 0.9percent, at 2,377.6.   In the futures markets, the June FT-SE 100 index contractexpired at 2,379.0, up from its close of 2,357.0 Thursday.   Some investors have been attracted by bargains uncovered by themarket's slide since Tuesday.   Additionally, traders reported some renewed interest in theadvantages of Britain's eventual entry into the exchange ratemechanism of the European Monetary System.   Volume was 324.1 million shares, compared with 278.5 millionshares at the same time on Thursday.</TEXT></DOC>